Parameters:

Returns:

encodeFontStyle

public static java.lang.String encodeFontStyle(int style)
Returns a string representation of the font style.
The result is one of the following:
  • PLAIN
  • BOLD
  • ITALIC
  • BOLDITALIC

Parameters:
style - The style in java.awt.Font.
Returns:
PLAIN, BOLD, ITALIC or BOLDITALIC.

decodeFont

public static java.awt.Font decodeFont(java.lang.String fontname,
                                       java.lang.String size,
                                       java.lang.String style)
Creates a Font from some human-readable information.

Parameters:
fontname - The name of the font.
size - The point size of the font in pixels
style - The style. This should contain one or more of the words "plain", "italic", "bold". For example "bold" is a valid style, "italic" is valid too and "bold italic" or "italic bold" mean the conjunctions of them. Any invalid style results in "plain".
Returns:
A Font object representing the meant font.
See Also:
Font.decode(java.lang.String)
